definitions.definition: Covered in pavement ; having a hard surface, as of concrete or asphalt .
Laid out or made, as intentions, desires, plans, etc.
examples: The road to Hell is paved with good intentions.

main_definition: Covered in pavement ; having a hard surface, as of concrete or asphalt .
secondary_definitions: ( figuratively ) Laid out or made, as intentions, desires, plans, etc.
